Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Peel and cut the @carrot{1}(peeled and cut into ½-inch cubes) into ½-inch cubes. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%box}. Wrap the @garlic cloves{2} in a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{for drizzling}.

Toss the chickpeas, @cauliflower florets{12%ounce}, and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, the @ras el hanout{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place the baking sheet and foil-wrapped garlic in the oven. Bake about ~{20%minutes}, tossing the veggies halfway through, until golden brown. The garlic should be very soft at this point.

While the veggies roast, bring 1 cup water with a large pinch of salt to a boil in a small #pot{}. Once boiling, add the @quinoa{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce to a simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender.

Halve the @lemon{1}. Use a #fork{} to mash the roasted garlic into a paste on your #cutting board{}. In a small #bowl{}, whisk together the lemon juice, garlic paste, @honey{1%teaspoon}, and about @olive oil{2%tablespoons}. Season with salt and pepper.

Toss: In a large bowl, toss together the quinoa, chickpeas, cauliflower, carrots, @arugula{2%ounce}, and vinaigrette. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate: Divide the crispy chickpea and roasted cauliflower salad between plates. Pick the @parsley{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked) leaves off the stems, sprinkle over, and enjoy!